&lt;/div&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/lifehacker/vip/~4/4BRYJXhiozE" height="1" width="1"&gt;</summary><author><name>Melanie Pinola</name></author><gr:likingUser>08076126602418447196</gr:likingUser><gr:likingUser>15835440548890645348</gr:likingUser><gr:likingUser>06405729912562463760</gr:likingUser><gr:likingUser>03379479171250075693</gr:likingUser><gr:likingUser>06925351185350905271</gr:likingUser><gr:likingUser>01700621362355095057</gr:likingUser><gr:likingUser>02030697187052009006</gr:likingUser><gr:likingUser>04561095782341368598</gr:likingUser><gr:likingUser>08008925857070562778</gr:likingUser><gr:likingUser>01904540286156864508</gr:likingUser><gr:likingUser>14204415836407914381</gr:likingUser><gr:likingUser>13150149342208419697</gr:likingUser><gr:likingUser>02053420159966049693</gr:likingUser><gr:likingUser>13137113934162262197</gr:likingUser><gr:likingUser>17444479066396751373</gr:likingUser><source gr:stream-id="feed/http://feeds.gawker.com/lifehacker/vip"><id>tag:google.com,2005:reader/feed/http://feeds.gawker.com/lifehacker/vip</id><title type="html">Lifehacker</title><link rel="alternate" href="http://lifehacker.com" type="text/html"/></source></entry><entry gr:crawl-timestamp-msec="1317317621374"><id gr:original-id="Lifehacker-5845035">tag:google.com,2005:reader/item/722df3e8b31be023</id><category term="Career"/><category term="Jobs"/><category term="Life Planning"/><category term="Printables"/><category term="Top"/><category term="Work"/><title type="html">Plan Your Career Like You Would a Four-Phase Project [Career]</title><published>2011-09-29T13:30:00Z</published><updated>2011-09-29T13:30:00Z</updated><link rel="alternate" href="http://feeds.gawker.com/~r/lifehacker/vip/~3/zAw0mEpE9dU/plan-your-career-like-a-four+phase-project" type="text/html"/><summary xml:base="http://lifehacker.com/" type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;a rel="lytebox" href="http://cache.gawkerassets.com/assets/images/17/2011/09/career-plan.jpg"&gt;&lt;img src="http://cache.gawker.com/assets/images/lifehacker/2011/09/career-plan.jpg" width="500" alt="Plan Your Career Like You Would a Four-Phase Project" title="Plan Your Career Like You Would a Four-Phase Project"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Many of us are great at carrying out work or individual projects from start to finish—the whole shebang. For our life-long careers and dreams, however, we&amp;#39;re less likely to have a plan with concrete milestones and steps in place. Mapping out where you want to go with your career, however, could help you achieve greater success. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IT Business Edge provides a project guide for creating a career development plan. Although it's geared towards IT professionals, the concepts and tools are applicable to most careers. For example, the four phases of this career plan include: self-reflection (figure out your strengths and attributes), develop your career plan (visualize where you want to go), implement your plan, and establish your credibility.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The project guide contains flowcharts and checklists downloads (in Word) to help you think through these steps. (You'll need to register to download the tools, but it's free.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.itbusinessedge.com/projects/it-career-development-plan/91409"&gt;IT Career Development Plan&lt;/a&gt; | IT Business Edge&lt;/p&gt;
